# Browser tools (preferred for frontend verification)

When a task touches frontend/UI behavior, prefer using Cursor browser tools to inspect and verify changes.

## If browser tools are unavailable
- Ask the developer to enable Browser Automation in Cursor settings.
- Suggested path: **Settings → Tools & MCP → Browser Automation**.
- Select the active Chrome tab that shows the target page.
- Start a new chat/session so the tools attach.

## Reloading pages (browser tools)
- Use the browser tool to send **Ctrl+Shift+R** for a hard reload in the connected tab.
